 Shanti, Harendra.","Indian (Uttar Pradesh): Brahmin name, from Sanskrit <i>om</i>, the Hindu sacred and mystic syllable uttered at the beginning of prayers.","Cambodian: written ឱម, corresponding to the exclamation of solemn affirmation, of Sanskrit origin (see 1 above), chanted by Buddhist monks."],"variants":[{"name":"Oum","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Southeast Asian Heang, Hye, Kam, Kan, Kheng, Khin, Kun, Sang, Sok, Phong, Yom, Yoo, Youn, Cuong, Phal, Samnang, Tin.  Cambodian Sokha, Chheang, Choeun, Moeun, Roeun, Sambath, Samoeun, Savuth, Soeun, Sopheap.","Cambodian: written អ៊ុំ, from a Khmer word denoting an elder sibling of one's parent (i.e. ‘uncle’ or ‘aunt’). Compare   Om   3 and   Um   2."]}]},{"name":"Devon","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from the name of the county of Devon, which originates from an ancient British tribal name, Latin <i>Dumnonii</i>, perhaps meaning ‘worshipers of the god Dumnonos’. Compare   Devonshire  .","Irish (County Louth): variant of   Devine  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Devenish","meanings":["English: habitational name from Anglo-Norman French <i>Deveneis</i>, Middle English <i>Devenish</i> ‘of or from Devon’. See also   Devon   and   Devonshire  , compare   Devonish  ."]},{"name":"Devonshire","meanings":["English: habitational name from the county of Devon, also known as Devonshire (see   Devon  ). Compare   Devonish  ."]}]},{"name":"Susannah","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Susanna  , in  2003  the most common in this group of names. It is the form of the name used in the Old Testament. The tale of Susannah, wife of  Joachim , and the elders who falsely accused her of adultery, is to be found in the apocryphal book that bears her name, and was popular in the Middle Ages and later."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Susannah of Devon was born in 1210, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. She married Sir William Paul Godisford. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1210–":"1210–Surnud","1205–1287":"1205–1287","1250–1330":"1250–1330","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1205":"1205","1210":"1210","1287":"1287","1330":"1330","1250":"1250","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"1210–":"1210–Kuollut","1205–1287":"1205–1287","1250–1330":"1250–1330","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1205":"1205","1210":"1210","1287":"1287","1330":"1330","1250":"1250","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"1210–":"1210–Décédée","1205–1287":"1205–1287","1250–1330":"1250–1330","1210–Female":"1210–Décédée","1205":"1205","1210":"1210","1287":"1287","1330":"1330","1250":"1250","Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Susannah of Devon est née en 1210, à Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Sir William Paul Godisford. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1210–":"1210–Verstorben","1205–1287":"1205–1287","1250–1330":"1250–1330","1210–Female":"1210–Verstorben","1205":"1205","1210":"1210","1287":"1287","1330":"1330","1250":"1250","Devon, England":"Devon, England","lifeSummary":"Susannah of Devon wurde 1210 in Devon, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hat Sir William Paul Godisford geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1210–":"1210–Desede","1205–1287":"1205–1287","1250–1330":"1250–1330","1210–Female":"1210–Desede","1205":"1205","1210":"1210","1287":"1287","1330":"1330","1250":"1250","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"hu":{"1210–":"1210–elhunyt","1205–1287":"1205–1287","1250–1330":"1250–1330","1210–Female":"1210–elhunyt","1205":"1205","1210":"1210","1287":"1287","1330":"1330","1250":"1250","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"id":{"1210–":"1210–Telah Meninggal","1205–1287":"1205–1287","1250–1330":"1250–1330","1210–Female":"1210–Telah Meninggal","1205":"1205","1210":"1210","1287":"1287","1330":"1330","1250":"1250","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"it":{"1210–":"1210–Decedu